        <updateDate>2007-11-29T20:55:26Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Restore U.S. Manufacturing Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a 100% tax deduction for qualified manufacturing activities income. Defines &quot;qualified manufacturing activities income&quot; as the excess of domestic manufacturing gross receipts over the cost of goods sold, and other expenses, losses, or deductions, properly allocable to such receipts. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Restore U.S. Manufacturing Act of 2007</title>
